Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

Just struggling to see what's the benefit of this. Downside is less definitive readability in code.

Why do we want to do this?

Patch Set 1:

> Just struggling to see what's the benefit of this. Downside is less definitive readability in code.

In what way is it less readable? The context can't have come from anywhere other than the request (with the exception of the admin context we elevate when needed, but that is already named appropriately).

> Why do we want to do this?

This makes lines shorter, especially when (in the next patch) we're going to access a lot of fields from the context, like request_id.

I would also say that this looks more conventional to me, consistent with a lot of other openstack code, where the context is peeled off from the request early in the API layer and passed around on its own.
